President Cyril Ramaphosa said the coronavirus has helped the state improve service delivery. He was in the Eastern Cape to assess the province's readiness to deal with the outbreak. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Consultations on the details of relaxing lockdown restrictions in the country to Level 3 will begin Friday. President Cyril Ramaphosa told the media during a visit to the Eastern Cape that the issue of the sale of alcohol and tobacco products will also be dealt with. READ: Ramaphosa announces plans for further easing of restrictions Ramaphosa strongly emphasised that the majority of the country would move to Level 3. "I must make it clear that we are moving to Level 3, many parts of the country will move to Level 3. EXPLAINER: The five alert levels post-lockdown "There are certain areas in the country that are hotspots, which we are going to be talking about, to demonstrate the incidents of infections," he said. The president said the country is not stuck at any alert level. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.